<title>USA: First Financial Corp sets special div.</title>
<headline>First Financial Corp sets special div.</headline>
<dateline>CUMBERLAND, Md. 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>First Financial Corp of Western Maryland, said on Thursday that it would pay a special dividend of $0.19 per common share.</p>
<p>The dividend, approved by stockholders, will be payable on May 28, to stockholders of record at the close of business on May 19, the company said in a statement.</p>
<p>First Financial Corp of Western Maryland is the holding company for First Federal Savings Bank of Western Maryland.</p>
